Reasoning: The paper discusses an approach to inferring the causal architecture of stochastic dynamical systems using rate distortion theory and causal shielding. This involves optimal causal filtering and estimation, which are related to information theory and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses model complexity and approximation, which are related to machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Statistics) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with the organization of structural scales, which is related to complex systems and network science, making cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the estimation of stored information, which is related to artificial intelligence and cognitive science, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
